<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/1252122-not-necessarily-about-this-book-but-a">Not necessarily about this book, but a question in general. WHY do people who review give a whole synopsis of the book? Don&#39;t you think readers already know this? Just a pet peeve. I just want to read the review! I don&#39;t care about reading two paragraphs about something I&#39;ve already read! Thanks.</a>
</div>
